\title{Stationary Distribution of a Markov Chain}
\taxon{definition}

\p{
  A \strong{stationary distribution} of a Markov chain is a probability distribution #{\boldsymbol{s} = (s_1, s_2, \dots, s_n)} such that

  ##{
    \sum_{i} s_i q_{i, j} = s_j
  }

  or equivalently

  ##{
    \boldsymbol{s} Q = \boldsymbol{s}
  }

  where #{Q} is the transition matrix of the Markov chain.
}
